## Architecture: Follow coinex (not coinbase)
Reasons: no datastore, simpler, more recent. Deviations documented below.

## Key Design Decisions

### Credentials (secrets.json)
AccountID is in Credentials (not Options) so user doesn't pass it on every run.
setup etrade subcommand discovers AccountID interactively and saves it.

    type Credentials struct {
        ConsumerKey       string `json:"consumer_key"`
        ConsumerSecret    string `json:"consumer_secret"`
        AccessToken       string `json:"access_token"`
        AccessTokenSecret string `json:"access_token_secret"`
        AccountID         string `json:"account_id"`
    }

Validation: Credentials.Check() returns error if any field is empty.

### Options
Sandbox bool selects the REST hostname via a restHostname() method.
No mandatory fields in Options (everything mandatory is in Credentials).

    ProductionHostname = "api.etrade.com"
    SandboxHostname    = "apisb.etrade.com"

    type Options struct {
        Sandbox              bool
        HttpClientTimeout    time.Duration  // default 5s
        TokenRenewalInterval time.Duration  // default 90min
        PollOrdersInterval   time.Duration  // default 10s
        PollPricesInterval   time.Duration  // default 5s
        PollBalancesInterval time.Duration  // default 30s
    }

### Auth: OAuth 1.0a, implemented manually
Uses stdlib: crypto/hmac + crypto/sha1 + encoding/base64.
No external oauth library — consistent with coinex's manual HMAC-SHA256.
Authorization header format:
    OAuth oauth_consumer_key="...", oauth_nonce="...", oauth_signature="...",
          oauth_signature_method="HMAC-SHA1", oauth_timestamp="...",
          oauth_token="...", oauth_version="1.0"
Token renewal: background goroutine calls GET /oauth/renew_access_token every
TokenRenewalInterval. On failure: logs fatal error, user must re-run setup.

### No WebSocket
E*TRADE has no streaming API. Three polling goroutines replace websocket:
  - goPollOrders(ctx)   — polls open orders, publishes to symbolOrderMap topics
  - goPollPrices(ctx)   — polls quotes, publishes to symbolPriceMap topics
  - goPollBalances(ctx) — polls account balance, publishes to balancesTopic
  - goRenewToken(ctx)   — keeps OAuth access token alive

### Client UUID / clientOrderId Problem
E*TRADE clientOrderId is numeric-only — cannot encode UUID into it (unlike coinex).
Solution:
  - Use atomic sequential int64 counter for E*TRADE's clientOrderId field
  - All UUID dedup done locally in clientIDStatusMap (same as coinex)
  - CanDedupOnClientUUID() returns false
  - internal.Order has ClientUUID uuid.UUID field, set externally (no json tag)
  - product.go maintains counterID->UUID map to recover UUID when polling orders

### Place Order Response
POST /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/orders/place returns PlaceOrderResponse.
Simpler structure than GET orders — no OrderDetail/Instrument nested fields.
Defined as separate struct in client.go. Does NOT use internal.APIOrder.
After place: only orderId known. Full details come from subsequent GetOrder poll.

### Fees
Commission = estimatedCommission + estimatedFees (both from Instrument level).
NOT using top-level TotalCommission (instrument level is more granular).

### Done Statuses
"EXECUTED", "CANCELLED", "REJECTED", "EXPIRED", "PARTIAL_CANCEL"

### Fatal Panics
If E*TRADE returns >1 OrderDetail or >1 Instrument for an order: panic with
the full JSON response body in the message. We only handle equity spot orders.

## internal/order.go Design
- Two-layer design: unexported nested API structs (apiProduct, apiInstrument,
  apiOrderDetail) for JSON parsing + public flat Order struct for interface impl.
- APIOrder is exported (used in client.go response structs).
- All API response fields included in nested structs; unused ones commented.
- NewOrderFromAPI() converts nested -> flat, panics on unexpected multiplicity.
- ClientUUID left as uuid.Nil by NewOrderFromAPI; caller must set it.
- FinishedAt() guards on ExecutedTimeMilli != 0 (cancelled orders have 0).
- ExecutedValue() = FilledQty * AvgFillPrice (computed, not stored).

## internal/quote.go Plan
E*TRADE quote endpoint: GET /v1/market/quote/{symbols}
Response field we care about: "lastTrade" or "lastPrice" for price, timestamp.
Must implement exchange.PriceUpdate interface:
    type PriceUpdate interface {
        PricePoint() (decimal.Decimal, gobs.RemoteTime)
    }
Model: coinex internal.BBOUpdate (which also implements PriceUpdate).
E*TRADE quote response structure (simplified):
    {
      "QuoteResponse": {
        "QuoteData": [{
          "dateTimeUTC": 1234567890,   // unix timestamp seconds
          "All": {
            "lastTrade": 150.25,
            "bidPrice": 150.20,
            "askPrice": 150.30,
            ...
          },
          "Product": { "symbol": "AAPL" }
        }]
      }
    }
Plan: define apiQuoteData (nested, unexported) + public Quote struct with
PricePoint() method. Include all fields, comment unused ones.

## internal/account.go Plan
E*TRADE balance endpoint: GET /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/balance
Must implement exchange.BalanceUpdate interface:
    type BalanceUpdate interface {
        Balance() (string, decimal.Decimal)
    }
Balance() returns (currency_symbol, available_amount).
For equity accounts: currency is "USD", amount is "cashAvailableForWithdrawal"
or "availableBalance" from the Computed section.
Model: coinex internal.BalanceUpdate.
E*TRADE balance response structure (simplified):
    {
      "BalanceResponse": {
        "accountId": "...",
        "Computed": {
          "cashAvailableForWithdrawal": 5000.00,
          "totalAccountValue": 15000.00,
          ...
        }
      }
    }

## E*TRADE API Endpoints Used
  GET  /oauth/request_token                              setup step 1
  GET  /oauth/access_token                               setup step 3
  GET  /oauth/renew_access_token                         background renewal
  GET  /v1/accounts/list                                 discover accounts (setup)
  GET  /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/orders                list/poll orders
  GET  /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/orders/{orderId}      get single order
  POST /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/orders/place          place order
  PUT  /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/orders/{orderId}/cancel  cancel order
  GET  /v1/market/quote/{symbols}                        get price quotes
  GET  /v1/accounts/{accountIdKey}/balance               get account balance

