## setup etrade Subcommand Flow
  1. Use ConsumerKey+ConsumerSecret to request OAuth request token
  2. Print authorization URL for user to open in browser
  3. Wait for user to enter verifier code
  4. Exchange request token + verifier for access token
  5. Call GET /v1/accounts/list, print all accounts with their accountIdKey
  6. Prompt user to enter which accountIdKey to use
  7. Save all fields to secrets.json

## server/server.go Changes Needed
In Start(), add etrade block after the coinex block:

    if secrets.ETrade != nil {
        opts := &etrade.Options{
            HttpClientTimeout: s.opts.MaxHttpClientTimeout,
        }
        ex, err := etrade.NewExchange(ctx, secrets.ETrade, opts)
        if err != nil {
            return fmt.Errorf("could not create etrade exchange: %w", err)
        }
        exchangeMap["etrade"] = ex
    }

Also update loadSecrets() check to include ETrade:
    if secrets.Coinbase == nil && secrets.CoinEx == nil && secrets.ETrade == nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("no exchange secrets are configured")
    }
